README

This folder contains scripts associated with the pinebiome metacode libraries

There are three scripts run on the crop diversity HPC:
#--------------------------------------------------------#

1. Pine-Metabar-QC-generic.sh
This script was run on each of the six sequencing libraries seperately. It runs fastp to perform basic filtering (trimming of poly-X tails and short reads).
Input: raw reads
Output: fastp filtered reads

2. Run-itxpress-generic.sh
This script was run on each of the six sequencing libraries seperately. It runs itxpress to remove trim reads to the ITS region
Input: fastp filtered reads
Output: trimmed and filtered reads

3. metabar_snakefile.smk & config.yaml
This is the main pipeline and runs qimme2 with dada2 denoise, sklearn for classification and performs additional filtering of mitochondrial and chloroplast reads.
In addition it performs appropriate merging of datasets after denoising into the timepoints for downstream analysis. 
Config details the parameters used. 
Input: trimmed and filtered reads
Output: qimme2 qza objects

The remaining scripts process the qiime qza objects in R:
#---------------------------------------------------------#

4. Gather_read_stats.R
This script parses the log files from the snakemake pipeline and outputs paired end reads throughout the filtering steps

5. Processing_qiime_artifacts_to_OTU_tables.R
This script takes the qiime qza objects and imports them into phyloseq. 
It goes through some basic filtering of outliers and contaminants from the synthetic community then outputs a RDS object and a tsv for use as OTU tables.

5. Summarise_control_samples
This script summarises the planned controls and then those that failed during library prep or sequencing. 

6. Summarise_tree_samples
This script summarises the tree samples and those that failed during library prep or sequencing. 
